  "text": "The ext_authz filter's bypass and passthrough logic is implemented across multiple C++ source files in envoyproxy/envoy. Here is a comprehensive analysis of the key components:\n\n## HTTP Filter Implementation (Primary)\n\nThe main HTTP ext_authz filter is located in `source/extensions/filters/http/ext_authz/`. The core bypass and passthrough logic includes:\n\n1. **Per-Route Bypass Configuration** (`ext_authz.h:322-394`, `FilterConfigPerRoute` class):\n   - Stores per-route configuration including a `disabled_` boolean field that controls whether ext_authz is bypassed for a specific route\n   - Handles CheckSettings with custom gRPC/HTTP service overrides per route\n   - Implements configuration merging for hierarchical route-specific overrides\n\n2. **Filter Bypass Logic** (`ext_authz.cc:400-451`, `Filter::decodeHeaders`):\n   - Lines 402-406: Gets per-route flags via `getPerRouteFlags()`, sets `skip_check_` if the route has ext_authz disabled\n   - Lines 404-405: Immediately returns Continue if skip_check is set, bypassing authorization entirely\n   - Lines 408-420: Checks global filter enable status and applies deny_at_disable logic\n   - This is the immediate passthrough path when bypass is configured\n\n3. **Per-Route Flag Resolution** (`ext_authz.cc:1160-1173`, `Filter::getPerRouteFlags`):\n   - Retrieves the most specific per-route configuration from virtual host/route/weighted cluster levels\n   - Returns PerRouteFlags struct containing the `skip_check_` boolean and check_settings\n   - Uses `Http::Utility::resolveMostSpecificPerFilterConfig<FilterConfigPerRoute>()` for hierarchical lookup\n\n4. **Authorization Decision & Immediate Response** (`ext_authz.cc:640-1104`, `Filter::onComplete`):\n   - Handles three CheckStatus results: OK, Denied, and Error\n   - **OK Path (681-968)**: Applies header mutations, clears route cache if configured (lines 686-691), increments ok stats, calls continueDecoding()\n   - **Denied Path (971-1045)**: Immediately sends local reply with 403 status and response headers via `decoder_callbacks_->sendLocalReply()` (lines 1018-1044)\n   - **Error Path (1048-1102)**: Respects failureModeAllow configuration - either fails closed (sends local reply) or allows traffic through with failure_mode_allowed header\n   - All response paths properly set response flags and statistics\n\n5. **Per-Route Service Overrides** (`ext_authz.cc:322-359`, `Filter::initiateCall`):\n   - Lines 323-358: Creates per-route gRPC or HTTP clients when configured\n   - Allows route-level override of authorization service endpoints\n   - Falls back to default client if creation fails\n\n## Network Filter Implementation\n\nThe network layer ext_authz filter in `source/extensions/filters/network/ext_authz/` implements similar logic:\n- `Filter::onData()` (lines 79-92): Checks filterEnabled metadata and calls authorization\n- `Filter::onComplete()` (lines 111-185): Handles OK/Denied/Error responses, closing connection on denial/error (unless failureModeAllow is set)\n\n## Common Classes & Response Processing\n\n1. **Authorization Response Structure** (`common/ext_authz/ext_authz.h:87-136`):\n   - Response struct contains CheckStatus (OK/Denied/Error), headers to add/set/remove, query parameters, body, status_code, and dynamic_metadata\n   - Supports immediate response path with custom status codes and headers\n\n2. **gRPC Client Response Processing** (`common/ext_authz/ext_authz_grpc_impl.cc:108-174`):\n   - `GrpcClientImpl::onSuccess()`: Converts gRPC CheckResponse to Response struct\n   - Lines 113-119: OK responses with mutations\n   - Lines 120-150: Error and Denied responses with custom status codes and headers\n   - `copyOkResponseMutations()` (lines 31-79): Processes response headers and query parameters\n\n3. **Configuration Factories** (`ext_authz/config.h/cc`):\n   - HTTP: `ExtAuthzFilterConfig::createRouteSpecificFilterConfigTyped()` creates FilterConfigPerRoute instances\n   - Network: Similar factory pattern for network filter configuration\n\n## Key Files Summary\n\nThe bypass and passthrough logic spans these C++ files:\n- **HTTP Filter Core**: ext_authz.h, ext_authz.cc (per-route bypass at line 403-405, skip_check flag)\n- **HTTP Configuration**: config.h, config.cc (route-specific config factory)\n- **Network Filter**: ext_authz.h, ext_authz.cc in network/ext_authz/ (similar bypass logic)\n- **Common Base**: ext_authz.h (Response and CheckStatus definitions)\n- **Response Processing**: ext_authz_grpc_impl.h/cc, ext_authz_http_impl.h (converts authorization responses)\n- **Request Building**: check_request_utils.h/cc (creates CheckRequest from HTTP/network streams)"
}

